"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523025","Department for Education","false","2016-06-13","<p>The percentage of pupils achieving five or more GCSEs at A* -C, including English and mathematics by local authority and disadvantaged backgrounds in 2014 and 2015 is published in the GCSE and equivalent statistical first release.[1],[2].</p><p> </p><p>Burnley district level information is not available.</p><p> </p><p>2015:</p><p>[1] <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/revised-gcse-and-equivalent-results-in-england-2014-to-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/revised-gcse-and-equivalent-results-in-england-2014-to-2015</a> (table LA9)</p><p> </p><p>[2] <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/gcse-and-equivalent-attainment-by-pupil-characteristics-2014" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/gcse-and-equivalent-attainment-by-pupil-characteristics-2014</a> (table 6)</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2016-06-13T16:05:22.503Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523025/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523025/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523025/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-06-06","GCSE: Disadvantaged","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many children from disadvantaged backgrounds in (a) Burnley and (b) Lancashire gained five or more GCSEs including English and mathematics in (i) 2014 and (ii) 2015.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","39364"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523026","Department for Education","false","2016-06-13","<p>The percentage of pupils who are eligible for free school meals and attain level 4 or above in key stage 2 reading, mathematics and writing, is published in the “National curriculum assessments at key stage 2: 2015,” statistical first release[1].</p><p> </p><p>Burnley district level information is not available.</p><p> </p><p>[1] KS2 for 2014/15:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/483612/SFR47_2015_KS2_LA_Tables.xlsx" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/483612/SFR47_2015_KS2_LA_Tables.xlsx</a> (Table 25 by local authorities)</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2016-06-13T16:03:34.053Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523026/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523026/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523026/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-06-06","Pupils: Disadvantaged","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how  many children in (a) Burnley and (b) Lancashire eligible for free school meals attain level four or above at Key Stage 2 in reading, mathematics and writing.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","39333"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523027","Department for Education","false","2016-06-14","<p>The following link provides the pupil to teacher ratio (PTR) in (a) state funded secondary and (b) state funded primary schools in Lancashire local authority and in England for November 2014, the latest information available: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/school-workforce-in-england-november-2014" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/school-workforce-in-england-november-2014</a></p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2016-06-14T16:03:47.97Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523027/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523027/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523027/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-06-06","Class Sizes: Lancashire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the teacher to pupil ratio is in (a) secondary and (b) primary schools in Lancashire.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","39332"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523028","Department for Education","false","2016-07-07","<p>The Department does not hold pupil level data on languages for the year 2000. In the January 2015 school census, the most common languages to which pupils of compulsory school age and above are exposed outside school and the number and proportion of pupils exposed to them are given in the table below.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Language</p></td><td><p>Number of Pupils (1)</p></td><td><p>Percentage of all pupils</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>English</p></td><td><p>5,634,349</p></td><td><p>82.1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Urdu</p></td><td><p>123,530</p></td><td><p>1.8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Panjabi</p></td><td><p>91,406</p></td><td><p>1.3</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Polish</p></td><td><p>90,506</p></td><td><p>1.3</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Other than English (not specified)</p></td><td><p>84,139</p></td><td><p>1.2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Bengali</p></td><td><p>74,635</p></td><td><p>1.1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Somali</p></td><td><p>46,361</p></td><td><p>0.7</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Arabic</p></td><td><p>41,951</p></td><td><p>0.6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Gujarati</p></td><td><p>40,735</p></td><td><p>0.6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Portuguese</p></td><td><p>29,759</p></td><td><p>0.4</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Tamil</p></td><td><p>29,634</p></td><td><p>0.4</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Believed to be other than English (not specified)</p></td><td><p>29,221</p></td><td><p>0.4</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>French</p></td><td><p>26,290</p></td><td><p>0.4</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Source: School Census January 2015<br>(1) Includes sole and dual main registered pupils of compulsory school age and above. Includes pupils in all state-funded schools excluding general hospital schools and local authority alternative provision.</p><p> </p><p>The languages recorded in the school census only indicate a pupil’s exposure to a non-English language outside of school. They are not a measure of English speaking proficiency, an indication of the language spoken in school, or a direct measure of immigration.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2016-07-07T15:07:07.417Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523028/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523028/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523028/answer","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523028/answer/previousversion/2869","Biography information for Nick Gibb","60","Education","Education","2016-06-06","Pupils: Languages","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what were the 10 foreign languages most spoken by pupils for whom English is listed as an additional language in the annual school census in (a) 2000 and (b) 2015; and how many pupils were recorded as speaking each of those languages in each of those years.","false","Biography information for Mr William Wragg","Hazel Grove","William Wragg","39310"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523029","Department for Education","false","2016-06-14","<p>The Department spent £132.2 million to support schools to become academies over the 2011-12 and 2012-13 financial years. Further details are in the table below:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Month</strong></p></td><td colspan="2"><p><strong>Financial Year &amp; Costs (£)</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p><strong>2011-12</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2012-13</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>April</p></td><td><p>3,024,083</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>May</p></td><td><p>4,318,836</p></td><td><p>5,882,474</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>June</p></td><td><p>7,178,835</p></td><td><p>4,408,560</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>July</p></td><td><p>4,729,951</p></td><td><p>6,799,528</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>August</p></td><td><p>6,025,674</p></td><td><p>4,702,531</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>September</p></td><td><p>9,018,053</p></td><td><p>1,617,852</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>October</p></td><td><p>8,028,855</p></td><td><p>6,736,111</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>November</p></td><td><p>5,298,198</p></td><td><p>3,997,178</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>December</p></td><td><p>5,969,589</p></td><td><p>5,754,346</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>January</p></td><td><p>5,612,638</p></td><td><p>8,067,316</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>February</p></td><td><p>3,396,016</p></td><td><p>5,059,683</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>March</p></td><td><p>4,594,872</p></td><td><p>11,957,148</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Year Total</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>67,195,600</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>64,982,727</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p>There are a number of factors which can influence the amount spent each month, including the profile of the projects for which payments have been made. For example, converter projects would receive the standard £25k support grant whilst sponsored projects receive an additional school improvement grant. The current sponsored grant rates can be found on GOV.UK at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/511128/sponsored_academies_funding_advice_for_sponsors.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/511128/sponsored_academies_funding_advice_for_sponsors.pdf</a>.</p><p> </p><p>Seasonal variation can also be a key factor, as a number of schools prefer to convert at the beginning of a new term. This could see spikes in payment a number of months before planned opening.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson",,"2016-06-14T14:44:35.827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523029/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523029/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523029/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-06-06","Academies: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 6 June 2016 to Question 38393, what estimate she has made of the total amount awarded to schools in pre-opening support grants in each month in (a) 2011-12 and (b) 2012-13.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","39437"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523030","Department for Education","false","2016-06-14","<p>The information requested is published by the Department on a monthly basis and is available at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dfe-monthly-workforce-management-information" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dfe-monthly-workforce-management-information</a> which also includes non-Departmental Public Bodies and non-Ministerial Departments across the time period in question.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2016-06-14T16:06:29.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523030/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523030/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523030/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-06-06","Department for Education: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what proportion of staff in her Department were (a) payroll and (b) non-payroll staff in each financial year from 2010-11 to 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","39380"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523031","Department for Education","false","2016-06-09","<p>The national pupil projections are only produced for the whole of England and do not break down projected pupil numbers by local education authority or region. They are derived from the 2012-based national population projections for England produced by the Office for National Statistics (ONS)[1] who used assumptions which were considered to best reflect demographic patterns at that time.</p><p> </p><p>The ONS uses assumptions on the levels of future fertility, net migration and life expectancy in the production of their population projections. They use central assumptions for the principal projections and alternative high and low assumptions to produce variant projections.</p><p> </p><p>New national pupil projections, based on the ONS’s mid-2014 national population projections[2], are scheduled to be published on 14 July 2016. The timing and content of National Statistics releases are a matter for the Head of Profession for statistics. The month of publication was pre-announced in 2015 and the specific date of publication was pre-announced on 26 February 2016.</p><p> </p><p>[1] Mid-2012 ONS national population projections available at <a href="http://www.ons.gov.uk/peoplepopulationandcommunity/populationandmigration/populationprojections/bulletins/nationalpopulationprojections/2013-11-06" target="_blank">http://www.ons.gov.uk/peoplepopulationandcommunity/populationandmigration/populationprojections/bulletins/nationalpopulationprojections/2013-11-06</a></p><p>[2] Mid-2014 ONS national population projections available at <a href="http://www.ons.gov.uk/peoplepopulationandcommunity/populationandmigration/populationprojections/bulletins/nationalpopulationprojections/2015-10-29" target="_blank">http://www.ons.gov.uk/peoplepopulationandcommunity/populationandmigration/populationprojections/bulletins/nationalpopulationprojections/2015-10-29</a></p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","39371 ; 39372 ; 39373","2016-06-09T15:35:56.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523031/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523031/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523031/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-06-06","Schools: Immigrants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, with reference to the National pupil projections statistics release, published on 22 July 2015, how many people defined as migrants are included in the principal population projections in each (a) local education authority and (b) region in each year between 2015 and 2024.","false","Biography information for Mr William Wragg","Hazel Grove","William Wragg","39374"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523032","Department for Education","false","2016-06-13","<p>No civil servants at the Department for Education are employed through limited companies.</p><p>We award contracts to individuals or organisations through their limited companies but the number of those could only be provided at disproportionate costs.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2016-06-13T16:01:20.683Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523032/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523032/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523032/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-06-06","Department for Education: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many civil servants in her Department are paid through limited companies.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","39398"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523033","Department for Education","false","2016-06-14","<p>The total spent on non-payroll Contingent Labour staff (ie, Agency Staff (Clerical and Admin); Interim Managers; and Specialist Contractors) in the Department for Education and its Executive Agencies is published by the Department for Education on a monthly basis at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dfe-monthly-workforce-management-information" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dfe-monthly-workforce-management-information</a> which also includes Non Departmental Public Bodies (Equality &amp; Human Rights Commission and Office of the Children's Commissioner).</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2016-06-14T16:04:43.883Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523033/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523033/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523033/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2016-06-06","Department for Education: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how much was spent on non-payroll staff in her Department in 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","39467"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523034","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-06-13","<p>The Department is in the process of finalising its Annual Report and Accounts – the information will be available in public domain in due course.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-06-13T16:11:29.903Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523034/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523034/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523034/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-06-06","Department for Energy and Climate Change: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, how much was spent on non-payroll staff in her Department in 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","39468"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523035","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-06-13","<p>All Civil Servants employed by the Department of Energy and Climate Change are paid through the departmental payroll system and none are paid through limited companies.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-06-13T15:43:27.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523035/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523035/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523035/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-06-06","Department for Energy and Climate Change: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, how many civil servants in her Department are paid through limited companies.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","39399"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523036","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-06-09","<p>The department has retained advisers in relation to this matter, however any reports they have prepared are commercially sensitive.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-06-09T15:22:41.11Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523036/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523036/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523036/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-06-06","Nuclear Power Stations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, if she will (a) list the titles of and (b) publish on her Department's website all reports prepared by (i) officials of her Department and (ii) contractors for her Department since May 2015 on options for financing new nuclear power plants.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","39423"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523037","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-06-13","<p>The proportion of staff who were (a) payroll and (b) non-payroll staff as at 31 March in each year from 2010-2011 to 2015-16 is set out in table 1.</p><p> </p><p>Payroll staff includes permanent staff, Short and Fixed Term Appointments, inward loans and secondments (where on payroll). Non-payroll includes agency staff, specialist contractors and consultants.</p><p> </p><p><strong>Table 1</strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p><strong>Payroll</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Non-payroll</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><em>2011</em></p></td><td><p>92%</p></td><td><p>8%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><em>2012 </em></p></td><td><p>89%</p></td><td><p>11%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><em>2013</em></p></td><td><p>88%</p></td><td><p>12%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><em>2014</em></p></td><td><p>91%</p></td><td><p>9%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><em>2015</em></p></td><td><p>89%</p></td><td><p>11%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><em>2016</em></p></td><td><p>94%</p></td><td><p>6%</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-06-13T15:43:01.657Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523037/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523037/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523037/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-06-06","Department for Energy and Climate Change: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what proportion of staff in her Department were (a) payroll and (b) non-payroll staff in each financial year from 2010-11 to 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","39381"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523038","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-06-09","<p>During Sizewell B’s periodic shutdown, inspectors from the Office for Nuclear Regulation (ONR) examined the Licensee’s arrangements for maintenance activities, reviewed test and inspection records and inspected the plant and equipment. A thorough examination (or in-service inspection) of the reactor pressure vessel (RPV) was completed by EDF to confirm that it remains in good condition. An ONR team of technical specialists examined the results of the in-service inspections and they are satisfied that they demonstrate the continued integrity of the RPV and that the hydrogen flaking present in the Doel 3 and Tihange 2 reactors in Belgium is not evident at Sizewell B.</p><p> </p><p>ONR inspectors did not identify any issues that would affect the safety case for the restart of the Sizewell B reactor and its safe operation up to the next planned statutory periodic shutdown in 2017, and issued clearance for it to restart on 31 May 2016. ONR expects to publish its Project Assessment Report, detailing this decision, on its website.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-06-09T15:21:35.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523038/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523038/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523038/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-06-06","Sizewell B Power Station","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what information she has been provided by the Office for Nuclear Regulation to demonstrate the safety of Sizewell B nuclear plant restarting after in-service inspection of the reactor pressure vessel undertaken by EDF; and what assessment she has made of the implications for that process of hydrogen flaking present in the RPV Doel 3 and Tihange 2 reactors in Belgium.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","39427"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523039","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-06-09","<p>The UK Government has intervened in the legal challenge brought by Austria against the European Commission’s State aid decision for Hinkley Point C. We have always been confident that the Commission’s decision is legally robust and, as a party to the proceedings, we have now seen the legal arguments made by Austria in their pleadings to the European General Court. It is on this basis that we do not consider that Austria has submitted a challenge of any merit. We consider that the Austrian Government, although following the correct legal procedures in challenging certain aspects of the State aid decision through the Court, has been motivated by its political stance on the future of nuclear more generally.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-06-09T15:22:26.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523039/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523039/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523039/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-06-06","Hinkley Point Power Stations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, pursuant to the oral evidence given by the Minister of State for Energy to the Energy and Climate Change Committee on 24 May 2016, at Question 200, what the basis is for the Minister's statement that the case brought by the government of Austria in the European Court on the European Commission decision on state aid for the Hinkley Point reactor has no merit; and whether that statement refers to lack of legal or of political merit.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","39482"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523040","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2016-06-09","<p>The Civil Nuclear Constabulary has undertaken surveys of its staff in previous years but these have not been on a regular annual basis.</p><p> </p><p>The last survey undertaken was a Wellbeing Survey conducted in May 2015 and a general all staff survey is planned for 2017/18.</p><p> </p><p>It is the Civil Nuclear Constabulary’s intention to run all staff surveys bi-annually in the future.</p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2016-06-09T15:21:19.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523040/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523040/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523040/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2016-06-06","Civil Nuclear Constabulary","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, whether the Civil Nuclear Constabulary conducts an annual survey of its staff.","false","Biography information for Clive Lewis","Norwich South","Clive Lewis","39287"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523041","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-06-13","<p>The Government regularly reviews its quota allocation policy. In recent years it has permanently realigned unused quota from Producer Organisations and allocated the first 100 tonnes, plus 10% of any remaining uplift in quota resulting from the introduction of the Landing Obligation, to the small-scale inshore fleet.</p><p> </p><p>These changes equate to over 1500 tonnes, or an additional £3 million worth of fish, for the small-scale fleet in 2016.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2016-06-13T11:53:13.53Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523041/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523041/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523041/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-06-06","Fisheries: Quotas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what progress the Government has made on rebalancing the UK's inland water quotas to smaller, specific locally-based fishing communities.","false","Biography information for Cat Smith","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Cat Smith","39285"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523042","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-06-10","<p>The Government does not consider it appropriate to provide best practice guidance to local authorities on abatement notices. Noise nuisance is best dealt with at a local level. Local authorities should therefore be free to take account of local circumstances when determining how best to apply the powers available to them in relevant noise and nuisance legislation.</p><p> </p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2016-06-10T12:15:42.4Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523042/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523042/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523042/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-06-06","Noise","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what guidance her Department provides to local authorities on the (a) issuing and (b) geographical extent of abatement notices to homes affected by noise nuisance.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","39293"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523043","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-06-15","<p>The Animal and Plant Health Agency have issued export health certificates for 281 consignments of dogs to be exported to Hong Kong within the last 12 months, relating to 309 dogs in total. To date 266 of these consignments have been confirmed, relating to 293 dogs in total.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2016-06-15T16:46:25.7Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523043/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523043/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523043/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-06-06","Dogs: Exports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many consignments of dogs were exported from the UK to Hong Kong in the last 12 months; and how many dogs were exported within those consignments.","false","Biography information for Angela Smith","Penistone and Stocksbridge","Angela Smith","39331"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523044","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-06-09","<p>Animal welfare regulations in third countries are the responsibility of those countries. However, we encourage other countries to improve or maintain welfare standards including through being a member of international organisations such as the World Organisation for Animal Health (OIE). EU Member States are subject to animal welfare regulations covered by EU law.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2016-06-09T13:20:45.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523044/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523044/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523044/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-06-06","Animal Welfare","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps her Department is taking to prevent the trade of (a) greyhounds and (b) other animals to countries with little or no protection for animals rights.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","39319"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523045","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-06-14","<p>Core Defra publishes Workforce Management Information on a monthly basis. This sets out the number of staff who are a) on payroll and b) off payroll and the published data covers financial years 2010-11 to 2015-16. It can be found at the following link: <a href="https://data.gov.uk/dataset/workforce-management-information-defra" target="_blank">https://data.gov.uk/dataset/workforce-management-information-defra</a>.</p><p> </p><p>No civil servants within Core Defra are paid through limited companies.</p><p> </p><p>The figure for spend on non-payroll staff in 2015-16 will be published in the 2015-16 Annual Report and Accounts.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","39400 ; 39469","2016-06-14T09:20:36.593Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523045/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523045/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523045/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-06-06","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what proportion of staff in her Department were (a) payroll and (b) non-payroll staff in each financial year from 2010-11 to 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","39382"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523046","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-06-09","<p>The first UK Climate Change Risk Assessment (CCRA): Government Report was published in 2012 at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/uk-climate-change-risk-assessment-government-report" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/uk-climate-change-risk-assessment-government-report</a>. Along with consideration of other climate hazards, it assesses the risks and opportunities of warmer temperatures on society and human health. Work is underway on the second CCRA, which will include an up-to-date review of evidence on the effects of climate change including changes in temperature. The second CCRA Government Report and the associated evidence report will be published in January next year.</p><p> </p><p>The Department of Health also carries out assessments of climate change impacts on health, the latest of which is called The Health Effects of Climate Change in the UK, published in 2012 and available to view at: <a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/publications/climate-change-health-effects-in-the-uk" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/publications/climate-change-health-effects-in-the-uk</a>.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2016-06-09T09:43:30.427Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523046/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523046/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523046/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-06-06","Climate Change","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what assessment she has made of the potential (a) negative and (b) positive effects on (i) society and (ii) human health of an increase in air temperatures arising from climate change.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","39425"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523047","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-06-14","<p>Core Defra publishes Workforce Management Information on a monthly basis. This sets out the number of staff who are a) on payroll and b) off payroll and the published data covers financial years 2010-11 to 2015-16. It can be found at the following link: <a href="https://data.gov.uk/dataset/workforce-management-information-defra" target="_blank">https://data.gov.uk/dataset/workforce-management-information-defra</a>.</p><p> </p><p>No civil servants within Core Defra are paid through limited companies.</p><p> </p><p>The figure for spend on non-payroll staff in 2015-16 will be published in the 2015-16 Annual Report and Accounts.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","39382 ; 39469","2016-06-14T09:20:36.657Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523047/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523047/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523047/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-06-06","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many civil servants in her Department are paid through limited companies.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","39400"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523048","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-06-14","<p>Core Defra publishes Workforce Management Information on a monthly basis. This sets out the number of staff who are a) on payroll and b) off payroll and the published data covers financial years 2010-11 to 2015-16. It can be found at the following link: <a href="https://data.gov.uk/dataset/workforce-management-information-defra" target="_blank">https://data.gov.uk/dataset/workforce-management-information-defra</a>.</p><p> </p><p>No civil servants within Core Defra are paid through limited companies.</p><p> </p><p>The figure for spend on non-payroll staff in 2015-16 will be published in the 2015-16 Annual Report and Accounts.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","39382 ; 39400","2016-06-14T09:20:36.727Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523048/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523048/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523048/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-06-06","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how much was spent on non-payroll staff in her Department in 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","39469"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523049","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2016-06-09","<p>We are continuing to consider which aspects of the current Code of Practice might need revisiting.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2016-06-09T13:23:25.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523049/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523049/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523049/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2016-06-06","Primates: Pets","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, with reference to the Answer of 17 November 2015 to Question 15358, what recent progress has been made on the review into the Code of Practice for the Welfare of Privately Kept Non-Human Primates.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","39436"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523050","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-06-10","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office (FCO) is unable to confirm the amount spent on non-payroll staff in 2015-16 until the 2015-16 Accounts have been signed off and the National Audit Office has completed its audit. This information should be available after 6 July 2016 at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications%20" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications </a>.</p><p>In 2014-15 the FCO spent £5.9m on non payroll staff – a 24% reduction from the previous year.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-06-10T14:26:23.21Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523050/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523050/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523050/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-06-06","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how much was spent on non-payroll staff in his Department in 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","39470"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523051","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-06-13","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office does not pay any of its civil servants through a limited company.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-06-13T12:58:51.63Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523051/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523051/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523051/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-06-06","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many civil servants in his Department are paid through limited companies.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","39401"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523052","Home Office","false","2016-06-09","<p>In order to safeguard an individual’s personal information and comply with the Data Protection Act 1998 the Home Office is limited in what information it can provide when the request is made by someone who is not the applicant. The Home Office is therefore unable to provide the information requested.</p><p>All applications are considered on their individual merits and in line with the Immigration Rules.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2016-06-09T15:14:37.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523052/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523052/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523052/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-06-06","Hamde Abu Rahma","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, for what reason the application from Mr Hamde Abu Rahma to visit Scotland was rejected; and if she will instigate a review of that decision.","false","Biography information for Tommy Sheppard","Edinburgh East","Tommy Sheppard","39424"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523053","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-06-14","<p>The proportion of Foreign and Commonwealth Office staff who were a) payroll and b) non-payroll in each financial year (taken on 31 March each year) from 2012-13 to 2015-16 is listed below. We are unable to provide the requested information for 2010 – 11 and 2011 – 12 because non-payroll data is not available for those years. We are unable to confirm the figures for 2015-16 until the 2015-16 Accounts have been signed off and the National Audit Office has completed its audit.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>March 2013</p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Payroll:</p></td><td><p>98.4%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Non-payroll:</p></td><td><p>1.6%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>March 2014</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Payroll:</p></td><td><p>98.3%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Non-payroll:</p></td><td><p>1.7%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>March 2015</p></td><td><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Payroll:</p></td><td><p>97.8%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Non-payroll:</p></td><td><p>2.2%</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-06-14T10:14:48.11Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523053/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523053/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523053/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-06-06","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what proportion of staff in his Department were (a) payroll and (b) non-payroll staff in each financial year from 2010-11 to 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","39383"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523054","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-06-13","<p>This information is not recorded centrally and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2016-06-13T16:07:05.677Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523054/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523054/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523054/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-06-06","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Publications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how much his Department and its executive agencies spent on the publications (a) Who's Who, (b) Burke's Peerage and (c) Debrett's in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","39451"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523055","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-06-09","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office is currently working with the Ascension Island Government to identify the island’s infrastructure needs. This is the first step in identifying long-term requirements for Ascension.</p>","Rochford and Southend East","James Duddridge",,"2016-06-09T14:04:03.95Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523055/answer","Biography information for James Duddridge","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523055/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523055/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-06-06","Ascension Island","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps his Department is taking to develop a long-term strategy for Ascension Island.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","39456"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523056","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-06-10","<p>Officials in the Foreign and Commonwealth Office are in regular communication with their US counterparts to explore the opportunities for cooperation in surveillance and enforcement of Marine Protected Areas, including the British Indian Ocean Territory and Ascension Island.</p>","Rochford and Southend East","James Duddridge",,"2016-06-10T11:32:06.667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523056/answer","Biography information for James Duddridge","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523056/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523056/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-06-06","British Overseas Territories: Marine Environment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations his Department has made to the US administration to secure its co-operation in surveillance and enforcement of closed marine areas in (a) British Indian Ocean Territory and (b) Ascension Island.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","39458"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523057","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-06-09","<p>Ascension Island Government has embarked on a project to assess and cost potential improvements to the pier head. I take all matters relating to piers seriously.</p>","Rochford and Southend East","James Duddridge",,"2016-06-09T14:05:49.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523057/answer","Biography information for James Duddridge","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523057/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523057/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-06-06","Ascension Island: Piers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what estimates his Department has received for the cost of refurbishing the pier head at Ascension Island.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","39457"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523058","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-06-09","<p>The Government concluded an independent feasibility study in February 2015, and carried out a twelve week public consultation, the results of which we published in January this year. The Government is still considering its policy in this area and will announce developments to Parliament and the public in due course.</p>","Rochford and Southend East","James Duddridge",,"2016-06-09T14:03:15.02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523058/answer","Biography information for James Duddridge","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523058/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523058/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-06-06","British Indian Ocean Territory","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what the Government's policy is on the future of the Chagos Islanders.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","39440"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523059","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-06-09","<p>The UK regularly raises our human rights concerns with the Iranian authorities, both in London and Tehran, and will continue to do so. Iran’s human rights record remains a serious cause for concern, particularly its use of the death penalty, torture, treatment of prisoners (including appropriate access to medical care) and restrictions on the freedom of religion and belief. We continue to urge Iran to abide by its international commitments to ensure all Iranians enjoy the rights and freedoms they are entitled to.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-06-09T14:24:41.793Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523059/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523059/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523059/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-06-06","Iran: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations he has made to his counterparts in the Iranian government on violations of human rights through executions, torture and arbitrary arrests in that country.","false","Biography information for Martyn Day","Linlithgow and East Falkirk","Martyn Day","39446"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523060","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-06-13","<p>Colombia is named as a priority country in the Foreign and Commonwealth Office’s (FCO) Annual Human Rights and Democracy Report.</p><p>Human rights violations and abuses remain a concern, including sexual violence, internal displacement, forced disappearances and targeting of HRDs. I am concerned at reports that 63 HRDs were killed in 2015, a 13% increase from 2014. I raised this issue with President Santos on 12 May.</p><p>The FCO publishes twice-yearly updates on the human rights situation in Colombia on the Gov.uk website. The most recent report cann be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/colombia-in-year-update-december-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/colombia-in-year-update-december-2015</a>.</p><p><br>I welcome the Colombian Government's genuine effort to address human rights concerns. We support their efforts and have prioritised the protection of human rights defenders; the promotion of business and human rights; and the Preventing Sexual Violence Iniative (PSVI). We helped Colombia draft its National Action Plan on Business and Human Rights, published in December, the first outside Europe.</p><p>We are committed to supporting Colombia as part of the ongoing peace process negotiations to ensure the safety of its people and long term stability across the country.</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire",,"2016-06-13T14:35:00.413Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523060/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523060/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523060/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-06-06","Colombia: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent assessment he has made of the human rights situation in Colombia.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","39313"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523061","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-06-09","<p>The information requested is not held centrally and to obtain it would incur disproportionate cost.</p>","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington",,"2016-06-09T16:19:28.43Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523061/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523061/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523061/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-06-06","Scottish Government: Visits Abroad","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, which overseas trips by Ministers of the Scottish Government were supported by (a) his Department and (b) British embassies and consulates in each year since 2014.","false","Biography information for Ian Murray","Edinburgh South","Ian Murray","39335"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523062","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-06-10","<p>We believe that UK support to Bahrain’s reform programme is the most constructive way to achieve long-lasting and sustainable reform in Bahrain. While it will take time to see the full results, UK support is having a direct, positive impact on areas of concern. We continue to work with the Government of Bahrain to ensure momentum and progress on its reforms, for the benefit of all Bahrainis. All Foreign and Commonwealth Office programmes that support security reform are carefully considered in line with HMG’s Overseas Security and Justice Assistance Guidance in order to assess and mitigate human rights risks. Our assistance is specially designed to improve human rights standards and strengthen the rule of law in partner countries. These programmes are routinely monitored and evaluated on a quarterly basis to ensure that they are on track for delivery.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-06-10T13:45:46.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523062/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523062/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523062/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-06-06","Bahrain: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will make it his policy to implement the recommendation in the report by Human Rights Watch and the Bahrain Institute for Rights and Democracy, The Blood of People Who Don't Co-operate, published in November 2015, that the Government should suspend support for security service reform until the other recommendations of that report are complied with.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","39304"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523063","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-06-13","<p>The State Visit presents an opportunity for the Government to continue our engagement with the Government of Colombia on a wide variety of themes, including: regional stability; peace and security; trade and investment; science and education; and the environment.</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire",,"2016-06-13T14:46:55.913Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523063/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523063/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523063/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-06-06","Colombia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what issues the Government plans to discuss with the President of Colombia during his state visit to the UK in November 2016.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","39316"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523064","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-06-10","<p>We have received representations from both Parliamentarians and non-governmental organisations in relation to this case.</p><p>We are deeply concerned by growing restrictions on civil society in Egypt, including asset freezes and travel bans against human rights defenders and NGOs. I have frequently raised this with the Egyptian Ambassador and issued a statement on 22 March. Officials regularly raise our concerns with representatives of the Egyptian Government in both Cairo and London, most recently in May.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-06-10T11:30:43.333Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523064/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523064/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523064/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-06-06","Egypt: Non-governmental Organisations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations he has (a) received and (b) made to the Egyptian government on investigations in Egypt into non-governmental organisations and their funding which form part of Case No. 173 (2011).","false","Biography information for Neil Carmichael","Stroud","Neil Carmichael","39317"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523065","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-06-10","<p>We believe that UK support to Bahrain’s reform programme is the most constructive way to achieve long-lasting and sustainable reform in Bahrain. While it will take time to see the full results, UK support is having a direct, positive impact on areas of concern. We continue to work with the Government of Bahrain to ensure momentum and progress on its reforms, for the benefit of all Bahrainis. All Foreign and Commonwealth Office programmes that support security reform are carefully considered in line with HMG’s Overseas Security and Justice Assistance Guidance in order to assess and mitigate human rights risks. Our assistance is specially designed to improve human rights standards and strengthen the rule of law in partner countries. These programmes are routinely monitored and evaluated on a quarterly basis to ensure that they are on track for delivery.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-06-10T14:24:58.007Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523065/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523065/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523065/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-06-06","Bahrain: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, with reference to the report, The Blood of People Who Don't Cooperate, published by Human Rights Watch in November 2015, if he will review his Department's policy of providing funding for the training of prison and security officers in Bahrain.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","39356"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523066","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-06-09","<p>The visit of the Rt Hon. Member for Gordon (Mr Salmond) and the Member for Ochil and South Perthshire (Ms Ahmed-Sheikh) to Tehran in December 2015 was organised and paid for entirely by the Scottish National Party and the Iranian authorities. The Foreign and Commonwealth Office provided some logistical support and Mr Salmond was briefed by the British Chargé d’affaires in Tehran on his arrival.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-06-09T14:18:43.413Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523066/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523066/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523066/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-06-06","Iran: Visits Abroad","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what support his Department provided to the delegation to Iran led by the Rt. hon. Member for Gordon and the hon. Member for Ochil and South Perthshire in December 2015.","false","Biography information for Ian Murray","Edinburgh South","Ian Murray","39370"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523067","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-06-13","<p>My Department is working closely with the FCO, BIS, the US Government, UKTI and the UK music industry to maximise opportunities for emerging and established musicians to perform to audiences in the United States and around the world. I recognise the US government's desire to strike the right balance between cultural exchange, creative exports and security. I hope together we can pursue practical improvements to the visa system which enable British talent to flourish in the US and around the world</p><p><br> ​Between 2012 and 2016, the Government invested £460 million in a range of music and cultural education programmes. We introduced tax relief for orchestras and started a successful music export scheme which has helped many musicians to go abroad.​ Discussions are ongoing about a revamp of the Music Export Growth Scheme and we hope to make an announcement shortly.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey","39060 ; 39061 ; 39062 ; 39063","2016-06-13T16:02:53.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523067/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523067/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523067/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-06-06","Musicians: USA","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what reports he has received on the costs, time taken and other difficulties related to the visa process for UK musicians performing in the US; and whether his Department has made representations on those costs and difficulties to the US government.","false","Biography information for Nigel Adams","Selby and Ainsty","Nigel Adams","39286"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523068","Department of Health","false","2016-06-14","<p>The information is not held centrally. As general practitioners (GPs) are independent contractors, it is for each practice to determine how they run their practice in order to meet the reasonable needs of their patients.</p><p> </p><p>The Department commissions a GP Worklife Survey and this is carried out by the Manchester Centre for Health Economics at the University of Manchester on behalf of the Policy Research Unit in Commissioning and the Healthcare System (PRUComm).</p><p> </p><p>In 2015, respondents were asked to indicate how much of their time was spent on external meetings, for example, meetings of the clinical commissioning group. Responses show that GPs spend 8.4% of their time on administration, 3.5% on external meetings and 6.3% on other activities.</p><p>The full report can be found at:</p><p>http://www.population-health.manchester.ac.uk/healtheconomics/research/Reports/EighthNationalGPWorklifeSurveyreport/EighthNationalGPWorklifeSurveyreport.pdf</p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2016-06-14T13:27:23.097Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523068/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523068/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523068/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-06-06","General Practitioners: Working Hours","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the average proportion of GP's working time spent outside of the surgery is.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","39291"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523069","Department of Health","false","2016-06-14","<p>An estimate of the cost of extending the current programme to boys has not been made. The Joint Committee on Vaccination and Immunisation (JCVI) is currently considering the option of extending human papilloma virus vaccination to adolescent boys. Once the JCVI has reviewed the available evidence it will report its recommendations. This will inform any future policy to extend the current programme to adolescent boys.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-06-14T15:04:14.053Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523069/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523069/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523069/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-06-06","Human Papillomavirus: Vaccination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate his Department has made of the cost of a quadrivalent vaccine programme for school-aged boys equivalent to that in place for school-aged girls; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr William Wragg","Hazel Grove","William Wragg","39297"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523070","Department of Health","false","2016-06-14","<p>The Department does not hold data on the average waiting time between cancer referral and diagnosis. NHS England collects data on cancer waiting times and these data are published on their website. The data comprise of organisational performance against operational standards that support waiting time commitments laid out in the NHS Constitution. These include the standard that 93% of patients should be seen by a specialist within a maximum of two weeks from urgent general practitioner (GP) referral where cancer is suspected. There are seven other cancer waiting time standards, but not one that measures waiting time between referral and diagnosis.</p><p> </p><p>A national time series can be found at the link below:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/statistics/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/02/Cancer-Waiting-Times-National-Time-Series-Oct-2009-Mar-2016-Provider-based.xlsx" target="_blank">https://www.england.nhs.uk/statistics/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/02/Cancer-Waiting-Times-National-Time-Series-Oct-2009-Mar-2016-Provider-based.xlsx</a></p><p> </p><p>The Independent Cancer Taskforce’s cancer strategy for 2015-2020 recommended a new standard that patients should be diagnosed with cancer, or have cancer excluded, within 28 days of being referred by their GP. Test sites for this new standard are in the process of being identified.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-06-14T15:09:46.653Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523070/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523070/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523070/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-06-06","Cancer","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what information his Department holds on the average waiting time between cancer referral and diagnosis in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","39298"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523071","Department of Health","false","2016-06-14","<p>It is estimated that up to 40,000 men who have sex with men (MSM) who attend genitourinary medicine (GUM) and HIV clinics will be offered the human papillomavirus vaccination.</p><p>There has been a positive response from those invited to participate, and confidence that the pilot will include a good geographical spread of providers, including those with the highest populations of MSM, as well as in rural areas with smaller MSM populations. Public Health England is currently completing the selection of the GUM and HIV clinics that will take part in the pilot.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","39300","2016-06-14T15:05:21.173Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523071/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523071/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523071/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-06-06","Human Papillomavirus: Vaccination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate his Department has made of how many men who have sex with men will receive the HPV vaccination as part of the proposed pilot.","false","Biography information for Mr William Wragg","Hazel Grove","William Wragg","39299"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523072","Department of Health","false","2016-06-14","<p>It is estimated that up to 40,000 men who have sex with men (MSM) who attend genitourinary medicine (GUM) and HIV clinics will be offered the human papillomavirus vaccination.</p><p>There has been a positive response from those invited to participate, and confidence that the pilot will include a good geographical spread of providers, including those with the highest populations of MSM, as well as in rural areas with smaller MSM populations. Public Health England is currently completing the selection of the GUM and HIV clinics that will take part in the pilot.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","39299","2016-06-14T15:05:21.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523072/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523072/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523072/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-06-06","Human Papillomavirus: Vaccination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many pilot areas his Department plans for the HPV vaccination for men who have sex with men; where his Department plans for those pilots to take place; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr William Wragg","Hazel Grove","William Wragg","39300"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523073","Department of Health","false","2016-06-14","<p>We are committed to ensuring that everyone at the end of life receives high quality, compassionate care that is tailored to their needs and preferences. The recent Royal College of Physicians’ audit showed steady improvement in the care people are receiving in hospital, but there are also areas where we could do better, including on ensuring round-the-clock access to specialist palliative care in hospitals, on record-keeping, and on involving people and those important to them in decisions about their care.</p><p>The Government will shortly publish its response to the independent Review of Choice in End of Life Care which will set out actions to improve quality, choice and personalisation of end of life care, including in hospital settings. We are working with NHS England to ensure the results of the audit inform this process.</p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2016-06-14T14:52:55.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523073/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523073/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523073/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-06-06","Palliative Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, with reference to the findings of the Royal College of Physicians' report, End of Life Care Audit: Dying in Hospital, published in March 2015, what steps his Department has taken to improve end-of-life care in the NHS.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","39279"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523074","Department of Health","false","2016-06-09","<p>In 2014/15, NHS England provided over £553 million of funding for the care and treatment of around 78,000 diagnosed HIV patients. A mathematical equation using these two figures would not result in an accurate cost for each new HIV infection as treatment varies according to clinical need and other factors such as age.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-06-09T11:37:11.18Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523074/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523074/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523074/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-06-06","HIV Infection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate his Department has made of the total cost to the NHS of each new HIV infection.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","39368"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523075","Department of Health","false","2016-06-14","<p>The Department has not made any estimate of the number of general practitioners (GPs) who have left the National Health Service since 1 January 2016.</p><p> </p><p>The Health and Social Care Information Centre’s (HSCIC) <em>General and Personal Medical Services: England 2005-2015, Provisional Experimental</em> workforce statistics published on 27 April showed that as at September 2015, there were 1,288 more full-time equivalent GPs working and training in the National Health Service than in September 2010. The HSCIC will be publishing these workforce statistics bi-annually, with data as at 31 March 2016 due for publication in September.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2016-06-14T15:44:28.543Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523075/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523075/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523075/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-06-06","General Practitioners: Termination of Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate he has made of the number of GPs who have left the NHS since 1 January 2016.","false","Biography information for Shabana Mahmood","Birmingham, Ladywood","Shabana Mahmood","39318"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523076","Department of Health","false","2016-06-09","<p>The Department does not hold data on the average waiting time between cancer diagnosis and treatment. NHS England collects data on cancer waiting times and these data are published on their website. The data comprise of organisational performance against operational standards that support waiting time commitments laid out in the NHS Constitution. These include the standard that 96% of patients should begin first definitive treatment for all cancers within a maximum of 31 days from diagnosis.</p><p> </p><p>A national time series can be found at the link below:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/statistics/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/02/Cancer-Waiting-Times-National-Time-Series-Oct-2009-Mar-2016-Provider-based.xlsx" target="_blank">https://www.england.nhs.uk/statistics/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/02/Cancer-Waiting-Times-National-Time-Series-Oct-2009-Mar-2016-Provider-based.xlsx</a></p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-06-09T15:13:35.217Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523076/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523076/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523076/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-06-06","Cancer","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what information his Department holds on the average waiting time between cancer diagnosis and treatment in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","39311"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523077","Department of Health","false","2016-06-09","<p>This information is not available centrally. This information may be obtained from West Midlands Ambulance Service NHS Foundation Trust. We have written to Sir Graham Meldrum, Chair of the Trust, informing him of the MP’s enquiry. He will reply shortly and a copy of the letter will be placed in the Library.</p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2016-06-09T10:23:25.053Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523077/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523077/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523077/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-06-06","Members: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will arrange for the Chief Executive of West Midlands Ambulance Service to send a reply to the hon. Member for Walsall North to his letter of 9 May 2016; and if he will ascertain for what reason there was no acknowledgment or substantive reply to that letter.","false","Biography information for Mr David Winnick","Walsall North","Mr David Winnick","39312"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523078","Department of Health","false","2016-06-14","<p>The Department considers a range of published statistics relating to smoking prevalence in England. These are drawn together in the Health and Social Care Information Centre report Statistics on Smoking, England, which is available at the link below:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.hscic.gov.uk/catalogue/PUB20781" target="_blank">http://www.hscic.gov.uk/catalogue/PUB20781</a></p><p> </p><p>The Integrated Household Survey gives figures for the other United Kingdom countries and is available at the link below:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.ons.gov.uk/ons/dcp171778_418136.pdf" target="_blank">http://www.ons.gov.uk/ons/dcp171778_418136.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p>Information on smoking prevalence in European countries is available from the World Health Organization European Region Tobacco Control Database at the link below:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://data.euro.who.int/Tobacco/" target="_blank">http://data.euro.who.int/Tobacco/</a></p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-06-14T15:06:38.137Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523078/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523078/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523078/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-06-06","Smoking","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what information his Department holds on the proportion of people in the UK (a) who smoke and (b) from other EU member states who smoke.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","39303"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523079","Department of Health","false","2016-06-14","<p>The proposals on which we are consulting will apply to all community pharmacies providing National Health Service pharmaceutical services in England.</p><p> </p><p>Our proposals are about improving services for patients and the public and securing efficiencies and savings. The Government believes these efficiencies can be made within community pharmacy without compromising the quality of services or public access to them.</p><p> </p><p>We have been consulting on the introduction of a Pharmacy Access Scheme, which will provide more NHS funds to certain pharmacies compared with others, considering factors such as location and the health needs of the local population.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2016-06-14T12:10:05.043Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523079/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523079/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523079/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-06-06","Pharmacy: Bradford","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate his Department has made of the number of pharmacies which will potentially be affected financially by planned changes to funding in the Bradford District Care Trust area.","false","Biography information for Imran Hussain","Bradford East","Imran Hussain","39330"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523080","Department of Health","false","2016-06-14","<p>Support services for people living with HIV are commissioned by local authorities.</p><p> </p><p>We are advised by NHS England that the boroughs of Lambeth, Southwark and Lewisham are currently consulting on a new service model, under which advice and advocacy, counselling and assessment and signposting services for people living with HIV would be provided by local non-HIV specialist services.</p><p> </p><p>We understand that the consultation exercise commenced on 9 May 2016 and is due to end on 28 June.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","39452 ; 39454","2016-06-14T15:08:33.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523080/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523080/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523080/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-06-06","HIV Infection: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment his Department has made of the (a) capacity of and (b) skills and knowledge of local mainstream advice and advocacy services in Lambeth, Southwark and Lewisham health authority area to be able to meet the support needs of local people living with HIV following implementation of the proposed reduction in specialist HIV support services.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","39453"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523081","Department of Health","false","2016-06-14","<p>Support services for people living with HIV are commissioned by local authorities.</p><p> </p><p>We are advised by NHS England that the boroughs of Lambeth, Southwark and Lewisham are currently consulting on a new service model, under which advice and advocacy, counselling and assessment and signposting services for people living with HIV would be provided by local non-HIV specialist services.</p><p> </p><p>We understand that the consultation exercise commenced on 9 May 2016 and is due to end on 28 June.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","39452 ; 39453","2016-06-14T15:08:32.96Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523081/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523081/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523081/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-06-06","HIV Infection: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what plans his Department has to meet the (a) advice and advocacy and (b) psychosocial needs of people living with HIV in Lambeth, Southwark and Lewisham health authority area following implementation of the proposed reduction in specialist HIV support services.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","39454"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523082","Department of Health","false","2016-06-09","<p>The amount spent on legal advice and representation is entirely a matter for local National Health Service organisations. There are no plans to introduce a central information collection for this information as the Department continues to work to reduce the burden of centralised data collection on the NHS.</p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2016-06-09T10:00:20.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523082/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523082/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523082/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-06-06","NHS: Coroners","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 26 May 2016 to Question 38058, if he will make it his policy to collect centrally information on the costs incurred by the NHS for legal advice and representation at inquests by cause of death.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","39501"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523083","Department of Health","false","2016-06-14","<p>Support services for people living with HIV are commissioned by local authorities.</p><p> </p><p>We are advised by NHS England that the boroughs of Lambeth, Southwark and Lewisham are currently consulting on a new service model, under which advice and advocacy, counselling and assessment and signposting services for people living with HIV would be provided by local non-HIV specialist services.</p><p> </p><p>We understand that the consultation exercise commenced on 9 May 2016 and is due to end on 28 June.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison","39453 ; 39454","2016-06-14T15:08:33.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523083/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523083/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523083/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-06-06","HIV Infection: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate he has made of how long a person with HIV will have to wait to access psychosocial support in Lambeth, Southwark and Lewisham health authority area following implementation of the proposed reduction in specialist HIV support services.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","39452"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523084","Department of Health","false","2016-06-14","<p>The Department has received various representations from Members of Parliament, Peers, stakeholders and some individual members of the public.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-06-14T15:06:07.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523084/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523084/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523084/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-06-06","HIV Infection: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what recent representations he has received on the possible benefits of pre-exposure prophylaxis for preventing HIV exposure.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","39481"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523085","Department of Health","false","2016-06-14","<p>The proportions of staff in payroll and non-payroll categories are presented in the table below. The information given is as at 31 March for each financial year.</p><p> </p><p>Payroll staff are civil servants who include employees, loans-in and fixed-term appointments. Non-payroll staff include agency workers, contractors and consultants.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="2"><p>Proportion of Staff</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>Payroll</p></td><td><p>Non-Payroll</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010-11</p></td><td><p>83%</p></td><td><p>17%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>87%</p></td><td><p>13%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>85%</p></td><td><p>15%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>91%</p></td><td><p>9%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>91%</p></td><td><p>9%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>94%</p></td><td><p>6%</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Recent, more detailed information, provided on a monthly basis, can be found at the web-sites given below.</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dh-monthly-workforce-information" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dh-monthly-workforce-information</a></p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dh-workforce-information-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dh-workforce-information-2016</a></p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-06-14T15:08:41.763Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523085/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523085/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523085/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-06-06","Department of Health: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what proportion of staff in his Department were (a) payroll and (b) non-payroll staff in each financial year from 2010-11 to 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","39384"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523086","Department of Health","false","2016-06-09","<p>Gluten-free foods are available on National Health Service prescription to patients with established gluten-sensitive enteropathies. The Department provides general practitioners (GPs) and other prescribers with a list of recommended gluten-free products to help patients, including those with coeliac disease, to manage their condition but does not issue guidance on the number of units that should be prescribed.</p><p> </p><p>Prescribing decisions are a matter for GPs and other prescribers. Clinical commissioning groups (CCGs) set local guidelines on the number of units to be prescribed for their patients, depending upon age, sex and individual clinical circumstances. A national charity – Coeliac UK – publishes guidelines on the dietary requirements for coeliac patients which can help inform CCG local decisions.</p><p> </p><p>GPs should always satisfy themselves that the medicines or other substances they consider appropriate for their patients can be safely prescribed and that patients are adequately monitored.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2016-06-09T10:14:35.013Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523086/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523086/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523086/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-06-06","Coeliac Disease","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the NHS's policy is on prescribing gluten-free food items to coeliacs; and whether any changes have recently been made to the allowance for such items.","false","Biography information for Gloria De Piero","Ashfield","Gloria De Piero","39426"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523087","Department of Health","false","2016-06-14","<p>There have been no such discussions.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-06-14T15:03:49.563Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523087/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523087/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523087/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-06-06","Strokes: Medical Treatments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what discussions he has had with the Royal Colleges on the introduction of microscopic magnetic bead injections for the treatment of strokes.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","39418"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523088","Department of Health","false","2016-06-14","<p>To reduce bed-blocking we are working closely with NHS England, NHS Improvement, Local Government Association, Association of Directors of Adult Social Services and the Department for Communities and Local Government, to provide a wide ranging package of support to help local areas improve transfers out of hospital and reduce delays.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is giving local authorities access to up to £3.5 billion of new support for social care by 2019/20. In 2016-17, there is also a new Better Care Fund requirement on local areas to develop a clear, focused action plan for managing delays, including locally agreed targets. The requirement is designed to reduce delays across the health and care system.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2016-06-14T13:28:33.877Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523088/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523088/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523088/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-06-06","Hospital Beds","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what recent steps he has taken to reduce bed-blocking in hospitals.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","39419"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523089","Department of Health","false","2016-06-14","<p>All civil servants employed by the core Department are paid via its payroll system.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-06-14T15:07:24.903Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523089/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523089/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523089/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-06-06","Department of Health: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many civil servants in his Department are paid through limited companies.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","39402"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523090","Department of Health","false","2016-06-14","<p>Data for 2015-16 will not be available until this year’s Annual Report and Accounts has been published.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-06-14T15:06:53.857Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523090/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523090/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523090/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-06-06","Department of Health: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how much was spent on non-payroll staff in his Department in 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","39471"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523091","Department of Health","false","2016-06-14","<p>The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) published interventional procedure guidance (IP) on transcutaneous electrical stimulation of the supraorbital nerve (which the Cefaly headband provides) for treating and preventing migraine in May 2016. Current evidence on its use raises no major safety concerns, but the evidence on its efficacy is limited in quantity and quality. The NICE has therefore recommended that this procedure should only be used with special arrangements for clinical governance, consent and audit or research.</p><p>IP guidance does not consider how much the procedures would cost the National Health Service, or whether the NHS should allocate funding for them. These decisions are made at a local NHS level and usually on a case-by-case basis. This means that if the NICE has issued guidance recommending any given IP, the NHS is not obliged to provide it.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-06-14T15:07:39.667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523091/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523091/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523091/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-06-06","Headaches: Medical Treatments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether he plans to make the Cefaly headband for the treatment of migraines available on the NHS.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","39420"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523092","Department of Health","false","2016-06-09","<p>Vote Leave is not authorised to use the National Health Service trademark, or an adaptation of it.</p><p>The Department has sought legal advice and has been in contact with the Vote Leave campaign about misuse of the NHS brand.</p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2016-06-09T15:54:51.137Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523092/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523092/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523092/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-06-06","NHS: Logos","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 6 June 2016 to Question 38480, whether his Department is taking steps in response to use of the NHS logo by the Vote Leave Campaign.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","39429"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523093","Department of Health","false","2016-06-09","<p>In the course of Government business, Ministers meet senior NHS England officials including the Chief Nursing Officer for England and the Chief Executive of NHS England on a regular basis to discuss policy formulation and current issues relating to the National Health Service.</p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2016-06-09T10:17:05.183Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523093/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523093/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523093/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-06-06","Health Professions: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 26 May 2016 to Question 37840, what discussions he had with (a) the Chief Nursing Officer for England and (b) the Chief Executive of NHS England about replacing bursaries; and what views those officials put forward in those discussions.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","39430"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523094","Home Office","false","2016-06-13","<p>Under the Firearms Act 1968, which applies to England, Wales and Scotland, firearm and shotgun certificate administration is a matter for the chief officer of police for the area in which the applicant lives. The time taken to process a firearm or shotgun application can vary as the chief officer must take into account the need to manage risk and ensure public protection.</p><p>The Policing and Crime Bill, which is before Parliament, introduces a power to issue statutory guidance to the police in relation to firearms licensing which should lead to improved consistency in practice across forces.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2016-06-13T14:48:14.02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523094/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523094/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523094/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-06-06","Firearms: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will take steps to reduce the time taken for a shotgun and firearm application to be processed.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","39415"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523095","Department for Transport","false","2016-06-13","<p>The Government does not collect specific data on the frequency of incidents involving drunk passengers on aircraft. As such, no estimates have been made.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2016-06-13T14:45:50.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523095/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523095/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523095/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2016-06-06","Aviation: Drunkenness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate he has made of the number of incidents of drunkenness on aeroplanes in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","39416"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523096","Cabinet Office","false","2016-06-13","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson",,"2016-06-13T08:14:13.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523096/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523096/answer","UKSA Response to PQ39417.pdf","UKSA Response to PQ39417.pdf","UKSA Letter to Member - Drink Related Incidents","UKSA Letter to Member - Drink Related Incidents","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523096/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-06-06","Alcoholic Drinks: Crime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many reported drink-related violent incidents involved the use of alcohol bottles in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","39417"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523097","Home Office","false","2016-06-13","<p>The Home Office publishes monthly spending data for non-payroll staff. This information is available online, and can be found here:</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/workforce-management-information-2016</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2016-06-13T15:16:11.35Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523097/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523097/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523097/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-06-06","Home Office: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how much was spent on non-payroll staff in her Department in 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","39472"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523098","Home Office","false","2016-06-24","<p>The Home Office have no civil servants employed that are paid through limited companies.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2016-06-24T13:04:14.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523098/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523098/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523098/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-06-06","Home Office: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many civil servants in her Department are paid through limited companies.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","39403"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523099","Home Office","false","2016-06-13","<p>Each Home Office Annual Report and Accounts publication includes information relating to payroll (civil servants) and non-payroll (agency and contractors substituting temporarily in civil servant roles as part of our flexible resourcing strategy) staff. Table 1 includes information for each of the financial years from 2010 – 11 to 2014-15. The percentage of non-payroll staff increased in 2012/13, 2013/14 and 2014/15 as the Department operated on a lower overall level of permanent civil servants, which was then complemented by more flexible hires to meet seasonal and other temporary demands.</p><p>Information for the 2015-16 period will be published shortly.</p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2016-06-13T15:55:16.543Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523099/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523099/answer","Table - 39385.xlsx","Table - 39385.xlsx","Home Office payroll","Home Office payroll","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523099/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-06-06","Home Office: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what proportion of staff in her Department were (a) payroll and (b) non-payroll staff in each financial year from 2010-11 to 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","39385"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523100","Home Office","false","2016-06-13","<p>This information is not available, except at disproportionate costs.</p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2016-06-13T15:14:39.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523100/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523100/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523100/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-06-06","Home Office: Publications","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how much her Department and its executive agencies spent on the publications (a) Who's Who, (b) Burke's Peerage and (c) Debrett's in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","39449"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523101","Home Office","false","2016-06-13","<p>New family Immigration Rules, including a minimum income threshold for British citizens sponsoring a non-EU partner, were implemented on 9 July 2012 to prevent burdens on the taxpayer, promote integration and tackle abuse.</p><p>We have continued to keep the new Rules under review and to make adjustments in light of feedback on their operation and impact. We have also taken into account the findings of the courts, including the July 2014 Court of Appeal judgment upholding the lawfulness of the minimum income threshold.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2016-06-13T15:46:09.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523101/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523101/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523101/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-06-06","Immigration: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what assessment her Department has made of the effect of (a) immigration rules in general and (b) income requirements on the eligibility of British citizens with non-EU partners to return to the UK and the incidence of family separation.","false","Biography information for Dr Philippa Whitford","Central Ayrshire","Dr Philippa Whitford","39422"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523102","Home Office","false","2016-06-13","<p>Border Force works very closely with law enforcement partners to harness the collective knowledge of risks associated with maritime and aviation security. This includes intelligence flows to Border Force and partner agencies from overseas partners, the maritime and aviation industries, voluntary organisations and the public. Border Force also works with the NCA through a series of Joint Border Intelligence units to share and develop intelligence across all modes including maritime and aviation.</p><p>The National Maritime Information Centre (NMIC), for which Border Force provides the executive lead, acts as the focal point for all agencies maritime information and provides the UK with unified maritime situational awareness to assist in countering potential threats to UK Maritime Security.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","39497","2016-06-13T15:06:15.673Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523102/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523102/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523102/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523102/answer/previousversion/2851","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-06-06","Shipping: Security","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps she has taken to improve the ability of Border Force to gather and exploit information to improve its performance in enforcing general maritime security; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","39496"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523103","Home Office","false","2016-06-13","<p>Border Force works very closely with law enforcement partners to harness the collective knowledge of risks associated with maritime and aviation security. This includes intelligence flows to Border Force and partner agencies from overseas partners, the maritime and aviation industries, voluntary organisations and the public. Border Force also works with the NCA through a series of Joint Border Intelligence units to share and develop intelligence across all modes including maritime and aviation.</p><p>The National Maritime Information Centre (NMIC), for which Border Force provides the executive lead, acts as the focal point for all agencies maritime information and provides the UK with unified maritime situational awareness to assist in countering potential threats to UK Maritime Security.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","39496","2016-06-13T15:06:15.753Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523103/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523103/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523103/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523103/answer/previousversion/2852","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-06-06","UK Border Force: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps she has taken to improve levels of knowledge within Border Force about the threats and risks associated with maritime and aviation border security; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","39497"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523104","Home Office","false","2016-06-22","<p>The security of our border remains a absolute priority. Border Force works closely with domestic and international partners on an intelligence-led approach to identify unlawful maritime activity including facilitation and illegal entry.</p><p>Information on vessels travelling to and from the UK is collected from a range of sources and analysed at the National Maritime Information Centre. The Government keeps all options relating to advance notification requirements under review and will continue to ensure proportionate measures are in place to secure our border.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","40057","2016-06-22T10:31:21.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523104/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523104/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523104/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523104/answer/previousversion/2848","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-06-06","Borders: Personal Records","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether she has taken steps to make advance passenger information available to Border Force general maritime officers; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","39493"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523105","Home Office","false","2016-06-27","<p>Penalties are issued for inadequately documented arrivals and it would not be known at that stage whether the passenger was an illegal immigrant.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2016-06-27T09:48:48.85Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523105/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523105/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523105/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523105/answer/previousversion/2849","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-06-06","Undocumented Migrants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many carrier liability charges were issued to commercial transport firms, airlines, ferry companies and other operators for transporting illegal immigrants into the UK in total by (a) port and (b) firm in each of the last seven years.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","39494"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523106","Home Office","false","2016-06-13","<p>Figures on asylum claims for Unaccompanied Asylum Seeking Children (UASC) are published quarterly by the Home Office in the Immigration Statistics release. The attached table shows the total number of claims for asylum from Unaccompanied Asylum Seeking Children, excluding dependants, in the last seven years.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total claims </strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009</p></td><td><p>2,857</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>1,515</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>1,248</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>1,125</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>1,265</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>1,945</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>3,043</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Notes</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="7"><p>(1) Data for 2015 are provisional and subject to change.</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="7"><p>(2) An Unaccompanied Asylum Seeking Child (UASC) is a person under 18, or who, in the absence of documentary evidence establishing age, appears to be under that age, is applying for asylum on his or her own right and has no relative or guardian in the United Kingdom.</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="7"><p>(3) Source: table as_08,<em> Immigration Statistics</em> January to March 2016, Home Office</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Annual figures on the number of claims for asylum from Unaccompanied Asylum Seeking Children by country of nationality are available in table as_08 in volume 3 of the asylum data tables: https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/525627/asylum3-q1-2016-tabs.ods.</p><p>A copy of the latest release, Immigration Statistics January to March 2016, is available from: https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/immigration-statistics-january-to-march-2016.</p><p>The information requested to answer parts (b) and (c) of the question is not centrally and systematically recorded and to provide this information would require the manual investigation of thousands of case files at a disproportionate cost.</p>","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire",,"2016-06-13T17:50:32.767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523106/answer","Biography information for James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523106/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523106/answer","Old Bexley and Sidcup","James Brokenshire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523106/answer/previousversion/2850","Biography information for James Brokenshire","1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-06-06","Asylum: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many unaccompanied children arrived in the UK and claimed asylum (a) for each country of origin, (b) by each commercial company who provided transport if known, (c) at each port and (d) in total in each of the last seven years.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","39495"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523107","Home Office","false","2016-06-16","<p>The Local Government Association (LGA) has worked in consultation with the Government to develop bespoke guidance for local authorities on the enforcement of the Psychoactive Substances Act 2016 and their new powers. This has been disseminated to local authorities across the country and is available at: http://www.local.gov.uk/web/guest/publications/-/journal_content/56/10180/7838372/PUBLICATION</p><p>In February, we held joint operational workshops with the National Police Chief’s Council for enforcement partners across the UK, including trading standards officers, to raise operational awareness of the Act.</p><p>We have also produced a forensic strategy for all enforcement partners on the new forensic requirements to support prosecutions under the Act.</p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2016-06-16T11:38:45.947Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523107/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523107/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523107/answer","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523107/answer/previousversion/2844","Biography information for Karen Bradley","1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-06-06","Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what guidance her Department has issued to local authorities on the Psychoactive Substances Act 2016.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","39305"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523108","Home Office","false","2016-06-15","<p>Unaccompanied migrant children are looked after by local authorities, which provide social work support and access to legal representation. Such children are also referred to the Refugee Council’s Children’s Panel for specialist support.</p><p>In addition, the Government ran a trial of independent child trafficking advocates from 8 September 2014 for a period of 12 months across 23 local authorities in England. The trial provided a valuable contribution to our understanding of this area of work and we are currently working with a broad range of interested parties as well as Parliamentarians to further develop our thinking so that we ensure we support trafficked children appropriately. We will update Parliament in due course.</p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2016-06-15T14:58:19.457Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523108/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523108/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523108/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-06-06","Asylum: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the Government's policy is on the use of child advocates to support social workers working with unaccompanied migrant children.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","39292"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523109","Department for International Development","false","2016-06-13","<p>The UK provides funding to the Central Emergency Response Fund (CERF), which was established by the UN and other leading donors to enable rapid emergency response. The CERF is doing an assessment of the situation following the rainfall and landslips in Sri Lanka.</p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2016-06-13T16:32:32.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523109/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523109/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523109/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-06-06","Sri Lanka: Floods","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, whether the Government will be allocating official development assistance to Sri Lanka in response to the appeal by the Sri Lankan government for international finance for reconstruction following the floods in that country.","false","Biography information for Ms Diane Abbott","Hackney North and Stoke Newington","Ms Diane Abbott","39288"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523110","Department for International Development","false","2016-06-13","<p>The UK Aid Strategy set out how the government’s aid budget will be restructured to ensure that it is spent on tackling the great global challenges from the root cause of migration and disease to the threat of terrorism and climate change, all of which impact the world’s poor and directly threaten Britain’s interests. The UK Aid Strategy sets out spending and reporting requirements.</p><p>All departments spending ODA will be required to put in place a clear plan to ensure that their programme design, quality assurance, approval, contracting and procurement, monitoring, reporting and evaluation processes represent international best practice. All UK ODA is administered with the promotion of the economic development and welfare of developing countries as its main objective, in line with the internationally agreed rules on ODA.</p><p>ODA-spending departments and funds must provide accurate and timely information on their ODA spending to DFID to meet OECD reporting requirements.</p>","New Forest West","Sir Desmond Swayne",,"2016-06-13T16:27:23.043Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523110/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523110/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523110/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-06-06","Development Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, whether other government departments are required to provide evidence to her Department that official development assistance disbursed by that department tackling global challenges is in the national interest.","false","Biography information for Mr Virendra Sharma","Ealing, Southall","Mr Virendra Sharma","39301"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523111","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-06-13","<p>We strongly support the ongoing peace talks between the Colombian Government and the Revolutionary Armed Forces of Colombia (FARC). I reiterated the UK’s support for the peace process when I met President Santos on 12 May, as did the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my Rt Hon. Friend the Member for Runnymede and Weybridge (Mr Hammond), during his visit to Colombia in April.</p><p>We have offered advice to the Colombian Government based on our experience in Northern Ireland, which is welcomed by President Santos. The UK supported Colombia in drafting and steering UN Resolution 2261 through the Security Council in January, receiving unanimous support.</p><p>Through Conflict, Security and Stability Fund, we have contributed £4.2 million to a UN post-conflict trust fund. The UN trust fund will increase the Colombian Government’s capacity and resources to fully implement the peace agreement, addressing issues such as food security, the removal of landmines and the strengthening of the judicial system.</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire",,"2016-06-13T14:44:54.99Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523111/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523111/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523111/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-06-06","Colombia: Peace Negotiations","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps his Department is taking to support the peace process in Colombia.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","39315"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523112","Department for International Development","false","2016-06-09","<p>The tender for the Pitcairn Islands supply ship is currently underway and best practice bio security and waste management requirement clauses will be included in the agreed contract.</p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne",,"2016-06-09T14:53:01.48Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523112/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523112/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523112/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-06-06","Pitcairn Islands: Shipping","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, whether her Department plans to include best practice bio security and waste management requirement clauses in the next contract for the Pitcairn Islands supply ship.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","39459"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523113","Department for International Development","false","2016-06-13","<p>DFID provides monthly workforce management information as part of its commitment to transparency. Information on staff numbers and costs is available at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dfid-workforce-management-information-public-body" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dfid-workforce-management-information-public-body</a>.</p>","New Forest West","Sir Desmond Swayne",,"2016-06-13T16:29:53.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523113/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523113/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523113/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-06-06","Department for International Development: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what proportion of staff in her Department were (a) payroll and (b) non-payroll staff in each financial year from 2010-11 to 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","39386"
