"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523132","Northern Ireland Office","false","2016-06-09","<p>As part of the Northern Ireland Devolution settlement, prosecutions under the Offences against the Person Act 1861 are a matter for the Northern Ireland Executive. I have no power to intervene in the Northern Ireland criminal justice system.</p><p> </p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2016-06-09T12:34:04.28Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523132/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523132/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/523132/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2016-06-06","Offences against the Person Act 1861: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, if she will make it her policy to hold discussions with the Northern Ireland Executive on the Offences Against the Person Act 1861.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","39307"
